<subSubSection pageId="114" pageNumber="393" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="114.[175,1381,3254,3480]" pageId="114" pageNumber="393">
<taxonomicName box="[178,314,3325,3358]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="114" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Peromyscus</taxonomicName>
oaxacensisis in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[568,652,3325,3358]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="114" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aztecus">aztecus</taxonomicName>
species group.It is considered by some to be a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[270,386,3364,3397]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="114" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="aztecus">P. aztecus</taxonomicName>
, but DNA data suggest it is a distinct species. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
